<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Male</emphasis>
(holotype): Total length 2.67. Carapace 1.51 long, 1.25 wide. Sternum 1.05 long, 0.86 wide. Leg measurements: I: 4.83; II: 4.44; III: 4.42; IV: 5.67. Carapace orange-brown with remarkable dorsal pattern of dark brown stains (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3A</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae, palps, and sternum orange-brown. Labium, endites and legs light orange, excepting coxae and tarsi pale orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3A, B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen dorsally dark gray, without stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3A</figureCitation>
), ventrally light gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3B</figureCitation>
). Anal tubercle and spinnerets pale light brown. Palp with large, pear-shaped tegulum, one-third of the cymbium length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3C, D</figureCitation>
, with retrolateral torsion (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6C, D</figureCitation>
), embolus long, anteriorly directed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3C, D</figureCitation>
), with a membranous keel at the opening and surrounding the embolus tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Drawings of male copulatory bulbs of Colombian Nopsma species. A, B. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo. C, D. Nopsma macagual sp. nov. E, F. Nopsma leticia sp. nov. G, H. Nopsma paya sp. nov. A, C, E, G. Retrolateral view. B, D, F, H. Prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.7 mm. Abbreviations: e = embolus, mk = membranous keel, t = tegulum." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566385" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">6C, D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">The specific name is a noun in apposition taken from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
Known only from the type locality (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution map of Colombian Nopsma species. Nopsma florencia Sanchez-Ruiz, Brescovit &amp; Bonaldo (circle), Nopsma leticia sp. nov. (triangles), Nopsma macagual sp. nov. (star) and Nopsma paya sp. nov. (polygon)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566387" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="383" type="preservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">Preservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="383">
Preserved in 80% ethanol. Male holotype in good condition, but abdomen is dry and shriveled (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3A</figureCitation>
). Both palps of holotype dissected in a separate microvial with partial damage on left cymbium tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Nopsma macagual sp. nov., male (holotype). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Left palp, prolateral view. Scale bars: A, B: 1.5 mm, C, D: 0.7 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.97.69089.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/566382" pageId="0" pageNumber="383">3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
